Pocket money. Are you kidding? A penny a week, a penny on a - on a Saturday, if you're lucky, or a ha'penny. It all depends if the old man was in funds or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12071385 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 You spent it mostly on books I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6714114 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 
Yes, I said - I wasnae a great sweet - I never was a sweet eater. So they went on books, like the Marvel, the Magnet and the Gem or something.
\par 
