\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12071385 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 Did they help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6714114 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 Oh no, they'd a big family. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12071385 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 What about any friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6714114 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 Oh the - the neighbours were a fine - as a matte
r of fact all the neighbours used to muck in sometimes. In these days you had to, it's a matter - maybe they would only come in if your mother was ill and do the fireplace and make a dinner or - or make it in their own house and come out and give you your
 dinner and so on. Oh they were very friendly and neighbourly in these days. Of course everybody was in the same boat I guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12071385 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7550569\charrsid10909046 Were all the people round about much the same?
